{"id":"6733","name":"Get Device Appearance [JS1]","tagline":"A JavaScript one-liner to get the screen mode (dark/light)","icon":"ios12 c255 g61525","latest":"21290","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>A single line of JavaScript to get to get the screen mode (dark/light). In iOS 14 is faster and easier to use the updated “Get Device Details” action with the \"Appearance\" option, but its output depends on the language used in the Shortcuts app. This shortcut does not depend on that, and also allows compatibility with iOS 12 (where \"Smart Invert Colors\" is detected as dark mode) and iOS 13.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No error checking</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://editor.scpl.dev/?scpl=%40Icon%20moon%20%2F*%20appearance%20glyph%20added%20in%20iOS%2014%20*%2F%0A%40Color%20darkgray%0AComment%20%22A%20JavaScript%20one-liner%20to%20get%20the%20screen%20mode%20(dark%2Flight)%20%E2%80%94%20%40atnbueno%20(2020-09-29)%5Cn%5Cn-%20In%20iOS%2014%20is%20easier%20and%20faster%20to%20use%20the%20updated%20%E2%80%9CGet%20Device%20Details%E2%80%9D%20action%2C%20but%20this%20can%20be%20used%20for%20compatibility%20with%20iOS%2012%20and%2013%5Cn-%20No%20error%20checking%22%0AURL%20%22data%3Atext%2Fhtml%2C%3Cscript%3Edocument.write(window.matchMedia(%27(prefers-color-scheme%3A%20dark)%27).matches%3F%27dark%27%3A%27light%27)%3C%2Fscript%3E%22%0AGetFileofType%20type%3D%22com.apple.webarchive%22%20-%3E%20mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%0AShowResult%20mv%3A%22Get%20File%20of%20Type%22%7Bas%3A%20text%7D\">ScPL source</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/matchMedia\"><code>Window.matchMedia()</code> documentation at MDN</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Don't download the shortcut</h4>\n<p>If you just want the code, there's no need to download the shortcut. Copy this and paste it in a \"URL\" action:</p>\n<pre><code>data:text/html,&lt;script&gt;document.write(window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches?'dark':'light')&lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Add a \"Get File of Type\" with type <code>com.apple.webarchive</code> below, and its output will be the word \"dark\" or \"light\". If you prefer another output (e.g. a zero instead of \"dark\", and a one instead of \"light\") change the <code>'dark':'light'</code> near the end of the line (e.g. by <code>0:1</code>).</p>\n<p>I use \"Get File of Type\" instead of \"Get Contents of Webpage\" to avoid that the user is misleading told that the shortcut uses Safari.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0 - Sept. 29, 2020, 1:42 p.m.</strong></p>"}